# Normalise line endings to LF in the working tree on every platform.
#
# This is load-bearing, not hygiene. The generator embeds the whitespace of the .razor source
# verbatim into the JS it emits, and the test suite compares that output byte-for-byte against
# committed answer keys and approved snapshots. With git's default autocrlf on Windows, a
# checked-out .razor gains CRLF, the generator faithfully emits createTextNode('\r\n\r\n'),
# and every snapshot test fails against an answer key that says '\n\n' — a green suite on
# Linux and macOS and a wholly red one on Windows, for a difference that exists only in the
# checkout. Pinning eol=lf makes the bytes the same everywhere.
#
# The stored content is already LF, so this changes the working tree, not the history — no
# renormalisation pass is needed.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary: never touch these.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.wasm binary
*.dll binary
*.nupkg binary
